 Music. Knowledge of Nietzsche's early literary writings further underscores the value of The Birth of Tragedy as a work of world literature. The present study makes available almost all of Nietzsche's early poetry and extensive excerpts from his early prose works and dramas - much of it in English for the first time - along with commentary. A final, extensive chapter on The Birth of Tragedy treats it as the culmination of the early literary works. The book contains many new insights into Nietzsche and his work and essential source material for future research. All "ations from Nietzsche are given in both the original German and in English.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aGerman Literature. 4aModern Literature. 4aPhilosophy. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / German.2bisacsh  aClassical Philology.  aDramas.  aPoetry.  aProse.  aThe Birth of Tragedy Out of the Spirit of Music.  aUniversity of Basel.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBoydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311143099740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781800108288?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781800108288423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781800108288/original  a978-3-11-143099-7  Boydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  aGBV-deGruyter-alles